WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:49.666 --> 00:52.234
Hang on. I know.

00:52.235 --> 00:54.269
Mm.

00:54.270 --> 00:56.605
You're doing so good.

00:56.606 --> 00:58.507
You're doing so good.
You all right?

00:58.508 --> 01:00.309
- Yeah.
- Okay.

01:00.310 --> 01:03.312
<i>Dr. Matthews to the nurses' station.</i>

01:03.313 --> 01:05.047
Excuse me.

01:05.048 --> 01:09.251
My wife's in labor.
We called ahead for Dr. Wheeler.

01:09.252 --> 01:11.843
I just need you to fill this out, please.

01:12.622 --> 01:15.349
- Thank you.
- Have a seat, hon.

01:22.065 --> 01:23.565
- I'll be right up.
- Yeah.

01:23.566 --> 01:27.158
- Okay?
- Okay.

01:27.637 --> 01:30.967
- Is this your first?
- No, no, it's our third.

01:30.974 --> 01:33.132
Sir, can you sign here?

01:34.410 --> 01:38.002
We're gonna name her Jessica.

02:07.911 --> 02:10.138
Vitals look good.

02:12.816 --> 02:14.449
Where's John?

02:14.450 --> 02:17.085
- Where's my husband?
- Just relax now.

02:17.086 --> 02:19.119
Everything's gonna be okay.

02:25.228 --> 02:27.629
What's happening?
What are you doing?

02:27.630 --> 02:29.198
I'm so sorry for your loss.

02:29.199 --> 02:31.466
- What?
- Your baby's dead.

02:31.467 --> 02:33.869
No, it's not dead. It's alive.

02:33.870 --> 02:35.938
What are you talking about?
It's moving.

02:35.939 --> 02:39.274
It's a terrible loss. We're so sorry.

02:39.275 --> 02:42.878
- Just relax.
- No!

02:42.879 --> 02:45.914
What? No, no, no. Put me to sleep.
I wanna be asleep.

02:45.915 --> 02:49.848
- It's too late for that.
- No!

02:52.956 --> 02:55.080
It's okay, you're doing great.

02:55.358 --> 02:57.492
What are you doing?
What are you doing?

02:57.493 --> 02:59.720
You might feel some tugging.

03:05.168 --> 03:07.970
Oh, my God. This isn't happening.

03:09.405 --> 03:13.075
Congratulations, Mrs. Coleman.
It's a girl.

04:28.551 --> 04:32.220
Yes, Kate, your dreams can be
a manifestation of your emotions.

04:32.221 --> 04:34.556
It's your body and mind's way
of dealing...

04:34.557 --> 04:37.225
with the stress and grief
of what happened.

04:37.226 --> 04:40.095
What if this has nothing to do
with the stillbirth?

04:40.096 --> 04:42.596
What do you think it's about?

04:43.700 --> 04:46.769
We're seeing kids
for the first time this weekend.

04:46.770 --> 04:50.827
And maybe the nightmares...

04:53.977 --> 04:57.944
Maybe I'm just not ready to adopt yet.

05:03.186 --> 05:07.483
I drove by the wine shop
on the way home the other night.

05:08.391 --> 05:09.791
Did you stop?

05:09.792 --> 05:13.795
No. Wanted to. The thought
went through my brain, you know?

05:13.796 --> 05:15.897
It wasn't for myself. It wasn't...

05:15.898 --> 05:20.035
I just thought it would be nice to have
a bottle handy, in case we had guests.

05:20.036 --> 05:21.864
But you didn't go in.

05:23.906 --> 05:25.407
Mm-mm.

05:25.408 --> 05:27.609
The key, to me...

05:27.610 --> 05:30.212
is not that you had the urge...

05:30.213 --> 05:32.047
but that you resisted it.

05:32.048 --> 05:36.118
You wouldn't have made it through
the home study if you weren't ready.

05:36.119 --> 05:37.753
But, ultimately...

05:37.754 --> 05:40.822
you have to decide.

06:03.546 --> 06:05.538
Hi.

06:06.182 --> 06:09.551
Honey, hello.

06:09.552 --> 06:12.254
Let me see. Ooh. Did you paint this?

06:13.456 --> 06:17.259
It's a beautiful butterfly.
It's fantastic.

06:17.260 --> 06:19.561
Really wonderful. Good.

06:19.562 --> 06:23.154
Let's go. I'm cold.

06:51.327 --> 06:53.490
Are you okay?

08:12.074 --> 08:14.066
Ah!

08:18.714 --> 08:20.116
Max!

08:20.117 --> 08:21.950
Max!

08:21.951 --> 08:23.818
Stop throwing!

08:23.819 --> 08:27.018
I'm working.

08:27.690 --> 08:29.124
KATE:
No, honey, I'm sorry.

08:29.125 --> 08:31.826
Just take a break
for a little while, okay?

08:31.827 --> 08:35.486
Because Mommy's trying
to play. Okay?

08:39.202 --> 08:41.501
Daddy's here.

08:44.707 --> 08:46.740
- Mine.
- Hey.

08:47.210 --> 08:50.011
- Hi.
- Sorry, practice went a little late.

08:50.012 --> 08:53.080
- It's all right.
- Whoa.

08:53.282 --> 08:56.817
- Okay, tough guy. Give me that.
- Wicked.

08:57.587 --> 08:59.087
No, no.

08:59.088 --> 09:01.723
Shoot it, shoot it. Go, go, go, go.

09:01.724 --> 09:05.594
- No.
- Yes! Give me five.

09:05.595 --> 09:07.729
Hey, how did it go? Daniel.

09:07.730 --> 09:09.688
Fine.

09:14.270 --> 09:16.570
JOHN:
Hey.

09:17.173 --> 09:18.373
Okay.

09:18.374 --> 09:20.442
DANIEL:
Five minutes. I'm at the last level.

09:20.443 --> 09:22.377
JOHN:
No more video games. Brush your teeth.

09:22.378 --> 09:25.247
That's no fair. It won't save.
Come on, Dad, please?

11:51.994 --> 11:53.195
Sorry.

11:53.196 --> 11:55.764
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

11:55.765 --> 11:57.359
God.

12:02.338 --> 12:04.235
You smell good.

12:15.484 --> 12:17.442
Okay.

12:18.287 --> 12:20.713
All right.

12:23.926 --> 12:27.496
I have to stop being like this.

12:27.497 --> 12:29.791
JOHN:
I get it.

12:37.373 --> 12:41.709
I'm very excited, I'm happy.

12:41.710 --> 12:44.437
I get nervous.

12:44.713 --> 12:47.474
I'm really scared.

12:49.885 --> 12:55.057
Last time I felt all of this
was right before I lost the baby.

12:55.058 --> 12:58.760
I don't want you to feel like we have
to go through with this for my sake.

12:58.761 --> 13:02.263
It's not just- It's not for you.

13:02.264 --> 13:04.532
I wanna take the love
we felt for Jessica...

13:04.533 --> 13:09.093
...and I wanna give it to somebody
who really needs it.

13:11.874 --> 13:14.442
Are you sure, hon?

13:16.545 --> 13:18.606
Yes.

13:39.502 --> 13:42.537
- Wanna make a snowman?
- Sure.

13:42.538 --> 13:44.537
It's really cold out here.

13:50.746 --> 13:52.547
Hey, stop it.

13:59.788 --> 14:01.656
- Hi.
- Hi.

14:01.657 --> 14:03.124
So glad you could make it.

14:03.125 --> 14:05.818
- So are we.
- Yeah, finally, right?

14:06.161 --> 14:09.992
- So good to see you.
- Thank you for coming.

14:10.767 --> 14:14.269
- This is really something.
- So go take a look around.

14:14.270 --> 14:17.431
- Stay out of trouble.
- Yeah, yeah.

14:20.242 --> 14:21.776
Look at the snow orphan.

14:21.777 --> 14:23.311
Snow orphan?

14:23.312 --> 14:26.180
Uh, snorphan?

14:35.925 --> 14:40.791
- Hey.
- No, show it to Sister Mary.

15:02.952 --> 15:06.521
- Slow down, slow down.
- You can't catch me.

15:06.522 --> 15:08.248
Yes, I can.

15:35.150 --> 15:37.479
Hello?

15:41.357 --> 15:43.247
Hi.

15:56.839 --> 15:58.840
Are all these paintings yours?

15:58.841 --> 16:03.172
- Yes. Do you like them?
- They're remarkable.

16:03.345 --> 16:04.912
Thank you.

16:04.913 --> 16:08.346
My name is Esther. What's yours?

16:08.350 --> 16:11.441
John. Nice to meet you.

16:12.221 --> 16:15.381
- Can I take a seat?
- Of course.

16:16.692 --> 16:19.961
I never get tired of watching
these kids enjoy the party.

16:19.962 --> 16:22.664
It really is. I'm so sorry
we didn't do this sooner.

16:22.665 --> 16:24.666
Don't be. It's a big leap.

16:24.667 --> 16:29.397
Adopting an older child
is not an easy decision to make.

16:30.372 --> 16:31.706
KATE:
John's in the bathroom.

16:31.707 --> 16:34.242
Think he'll find us?
Do you wanna go look for him?

16:34.243 --> 16:39.247
- Where did you get the idea for this one?
- My paintings always tell stories.

16:39.248 --> 16:42.750
This one's about a sad mother lion
who can't find her cubs.

16:42.751 --> 16:46.688
- She's smiling.
- She's dreaming about her babies.

16:46.689 --> 16:48.791
It's the only thing
that makes her happy.

16:48.792 --> 16:53.794
- I hope she finds them.
- She will. Look.

16:56.398 --> 16:59.767
They were lost in the jungle,
and they were so scared...

16:59.768 --> 17:02.071
...because they didn't have a mother.

17:02.072 --> 17:04.638
Just when they thought
they'd be alone forever...

17:04.640 --> 17:08.443
...they found their mother asleep
under this tree.

17:08.444 --> 17:12.113
Now when she wakes up,
her dream will have come true.

17:12.114 --> 17:15.818
- She'll have her family again.
- Amazing. You came up with that story?

17:15.819 --> 17:18.909
- I think I hear his voice down here.
- Yes.

17:19.621 --> 17:23.291
Hey. I want to introduce you.
This is my wife, Kate.

17:23.292 --> 17:25.257
Kate, this is Esther.

17:26.095 --> 17:27.859
Hello.

17:29.465 --> 17:32.898
How are you? Nice to meet you.

17:33.335 --> 17:35.770
She painted all these.

17:35.771 --> 17:36.972
- Really?
- Yeah.

17:36.973 --> 17:39.874
These are fantastic.
These are really wonderful.

17:39.875 --> 17:42.443
- Thank you.
- Where did you learn how to do this?

17:42.444 --> 17:45.813
I've just had lots of time to practice,
I guess.

17:45.814 --> 17:48.783
It's really boring here.

17:48.784 --> 17:50.953
It's boring here?

17:50.954 --> 17:53.788
If you're so bored,
why aren't you down at the party?

17:53.789 --> 17:59.053
I've never really seen the point of it.
Nobody's ever talked to me before.

17:59.394 --> 18:00.661
I guess I'm different.

18:00.662 --> 18:03.030
There's nothing wrong
with being different.

18:03.031 --> 18:05.166
JOHN:
Well, you two have a lot in common.

18:09.571 --> 18:11.673
ESTHER:
I think people should always...

18:11.674 --> 18:14.308
...try to take the bad things
that happen to them...

18:14.309 --> 18:16.844
...and turn them into something good.

18:16.845 --> 18:19.814
- Don't you?
- Yeah.

18:19.815 --> 18:22.115
Absolutely.

18:28.390 --> 18:32.060
She's originally from Russia, but it's
amazing how strong her English is.

18:32.061 --> 18:34.529
She's only been in the country
a few years.

18:34.530 --> 18:36.731
You get children
from other countries?

18:36.732 --> 18:41.435
It's rare. But when we do,
it's sometimes difficult to place them.

18:41.436 --> 18:45.407
The family that brought her to America
died in a house fire.

18:45.408 --> 18:47.008
In a fire?

18:47.009 --> 18:48.576
My God.

18:48.577 --> 18:50.701
Esther barely got out.

18:50.879 --> 18:55.583
She's been through a lot, but this
is an extraordinary little girl.

18:55.584 --> 18:58.719
She's very bright.
She's very mature for her age.

18:58.720 --> 19:03.024
And she's very well-mannered.
She's a bit of a princess, actually.

19:03.025 --> 19:07.425
She wears those ribbons on her wrists
and her neck all the time.

19:07.462 --> 19:08.696
Mine too.

19:08.697 --> 19:11.632
We had trouble with her
when we tried to take them off.

19:11.633 --> 19:13.634
How does she get along
with other kids?

19:13.635 --> 19:16.070
Oh, when she has to interact,
she's great.

19:16.071 --> 19:18.372
Babe?

19:18.373 --> 19:21.742
- She really did seem to open up with us.
- Yeah.

19:21.743 --> 19:24.712
I thought she more
than opened up with you.

19:24.713 --> 19:26.982
You seem to have made
quite a connection.

19:26.983 --> 19:31.746
I could get the paperwork together
and see you back here in three weeks.

19:37.459 --> 19:39.554
All right.

19:49.071 --> 19:50.304
Okey-dokey.

19:50.305 --> 19:52.506
Call me if you need anything.

19:52.507 --> 19:54.871
Bye. Okay, thank you.

20:13.962 --> 20:16.631
Oh, that's T~H.

20:16.632 --> 20:19.433
T~H. Yeah.

20:19.434 --> 20:21.703
And " Max" is like this?

20:21.704 --> 20:23.361
Yeah.

20:24.039 --> 20:26.031
Good.

20:29.978 --> 20:34.947
- Is this your house?
- Now it's your house too.

20:50.799 --> 20:55.267
Hi, sweetie.
Hi. Look who's here.

20:59.708 --> 21:04.211
Hello, Max. My name is Esther.

21:04.212 --> 21:07.144
She's been practicing the whole way.

21:08.684 --> 21:10.885
- Can she hear?
- A little.

21:10.886 --> 21:12.853
She was born almost completely deaf.

21:12.854 --> 21:16.652
That just allows her to hear enough
to read lips.

21:19.594 --> 21:22.263
That's all right, I got it.

21:26.501 --> 21:29.103
I'd like to introduce you
to Grandma Barbara.

21:29.104 --> 21:31.973
It's a pleasure to meet you.

21:31.974 --> 21:35.566
That's precious.
It's a pleasure to meet you too.

21:36.712 --> 21:38.779
Danny.

21:38.780 --> 21:41.575
This is Esther.

21:43.085 --> 21:44.880
Hello, Daniel.

21:45.487 --> 21:47.616
Hey.

21:50.860 --> 21:52.893
Why does she dress like that?

21:52.894 --> 21:56.230
- Come on. Stop it.
- I'm just asking a question.

21:56.231 --> 21:58.532
Oh!

21:58.900 --> 22:02.069
- You have a piano?
- Yeah.

22:02.070 --> 22:05.798
- Would you like to learn how to play?
- I would love to.

22:14.449 --> 22:15.649
Do you like it?

22:15.650 --> 22:18.412
- It's perfect.
- Good.

22:25.328 --> 22:26.761
Thank you.

22:26.762 --> 22:29.130
How do you say "thank you"?

22:29.131 --> 22:30.831
Thank you.

22:40.075 --> 22:42.977
Wow, look at that.

22:42.978 --> 22:46.148
What? What? What?

22:46.149 --> 22:47.581
Dad, look.

22:47.582 --> 22:49.283
- Dad.
- Where did you get that?

22:49.284 --> 22:52.453
- Dad, look, I'm killing Trevor.
- Great.

22:52.454 --> 22:54.344
Yes.

22:56.958 --> 22:58.426
Thank you.

22:58.427 --> 23:01.461
Come on, Dad. My solo's
gonna end, hurry, look.

23:02.431 --> 23:04.765
Wow, cool.

23:09.204 --> 23:12.466
- Trevor, you suck.
- Shut up.

23:13.443 --> 23:16.442
That's fabulous.

23:16.478 --> 23:19.580
Come on, guys. This is lame.

23:19.581 --> 23:22.411
I was just about to beat you.

23:22.784 --> 23:25.716
I'm glad you like it, honey.

23:42.370 --> 23:44.232
Come on, guys.

23:49.144 --> 23:51.645
Hurry up, I'm freezing my ass off.

23:51.646 --> 23:56.979
- Dude, it's all in here.
- Oh, God. My hands are freezing.

23:57.185 --> 23:59.153
Oh, man, she's hot.

23:59.154 --> 24:02.746
- Move over, man.
- Page 34 will change your life.

24:03.558 --> 24:05.755
Whoa.

24:06.128 --> 24:07.995
This looks like your mom.

24:10.232 --> 24:11.963
No.

24:16.239 --> 24:18.706
Esther and Maxine
seem to be getting along well.

24:18.707 --> 24:20.074
Yeah.

24:20.075 --> 24:21.943
How's she doing, Kate?

24:21.944 --> 24:24.445
Esther's fitting right in.

24:24.446 --> 24:26.247
I meant Maxine.

24:26.248 --> 24:29.050
She's playing by the pond
like nothing ever happened.

24:29.051 --> 24:30.885
She doesn't remember, does she?

24:30.886 --> 24:33.886
No. She's fine.

24:38.193 --> 24:42.029
So, what are your plans?

24:42.030 --> 24:45.656
You know,
probably get Esther settled...

24:45.901 --> 24:48.035
then go back to teaching.

24:48.036 --> 24:50.172
Thought they weren't gonna
take you back.

24:50.173 --> 24:51.805
No, I'm not talking about Yale.

24:51.806 --> 24:55.075
I'll just... I'll probably
give lessons from home.

24:55.076 --> 24:57.611
That's too bad.
That was a very good job.

24:57.612 --> 24:59.747
Well, I didn't quit
because I wanted to.

24:59.748 --> 25:03.083
I know. You had to have
your moment of clarity.

25:03.084 --> 25:06.209
That is an A.A. term.

25:06.388 --> 25:08.822
And I didn't go to A.A.
I just stopped drinking.

25:08.823 --> 25:13.018
Same difference. We all need
a wake-up call sometimes.

26:19.562 --> 26:21.553
Hi.

26:22.063 --> 26:25.757
- Hi.
- Come here.

26:43.285 --> 26:45.512
Yeah?

26:46.689 --> 26:50.157
- Oh, hey.
- We're scared of the lightning.

26:50.158 --> 26:52.253
Oh, come in.

26:52.661 --> 26:58.255
- I wanna sleep next to Daddy.
- Hang on.

26:58.900 --> 27:01.098
Okay.

27:09.644 --> 27:12.179
I'm gonna call later,
make sure everything's okay.

27:12.180 --> 27:14.549
Okay. They're gonna love
your design.

27:14.550 --> 27:16.583
- You gonna pick up the phone?
- Yeah.

27:16.584 --> 27:18.576
All right.

27:19.054 --> 27:21.056
Esther?

27:21.057 --> 27:22.923
Esther?

27:22.924 --> 27:24.825
Come on.

27:24.826 --> 27:28.430
Esther, come on, we gotta go!

27:28.431 --> 27:32.032
You gotta be kidding me.

27:32.033 --> 27:35.831
Wow. Uh...

27:36.037 --> 27:38.935
- Will you please go wait in the car?
- Come on.

27:42.211 --> 27:44.978
Sweetheart,
this isn't really a school dress.

27:44.979 --> 27:47.715
But I like it.
Don't you think it's pretty?

27:47.716 --> 27:49.483
Yes, it's so beautiful...

27:49.484 --> 27:52.753
...but I just don't think
you're gonna be comfortable in it.

27:52.754 --> 27:54.054
What about those jeans?

27:54.055 --> 27:57.091
You're afraid the other children
will laugh at me.

27:57.092 --> 28:02.153
I thought you said there wasn't
anything wrong with being different.

28:02.932 --> 28:05.432
Yes, you're right.
You're absolutely right.

28:05.433 --> 28:08.729
Okay. Have fun.

28:09.605 --> 28:12.373
Take a seat, please. Take a seat.

28:12.374 --> 28:15.101
Don't make me ask again, please.

28:15.443 --> 28:18.679
Okay, this is our new student.
Her name's Esther Coleman.

28:18.680 --> 28:21.982
And I'd like you all
to make her feel very welcome today.

28:21.983 --> 28:25.586
Oh, look. Little Bo Peep texted me.
She wants her outfit back.

28:29.124 --> 28:31.419
Okay, go take a seat.

28:32.660 --> 28:36.127
Okay, if everybody could turn
to Page 27...

28:40.435 --> 28:41.668
No!

28:41.669 --> 28:44.105
No! Esther, what are you doing?

28:44.106 --> 28:47.107
Get away from there! No!

28:47.108 --> 28:51.146
You don't play near the water!
You know that!

28:51.147 --> 28:53.043
Come on, get out!

28:54.015 --> 28:56.276
Max.

29:13.034 --> 29:16.296
Sweet. Bull's-eye.

29:17.172 --> 29:18.699
Got you.

29:51.841 --> 29:53.004
Did you kill it?

29:53.005 --> 29:55.773
It's just a paint-ball,
I didn't think it'd hurt him.

30:04.886 --> 30:06.954
Put it out of its misery.

30:08.022 --> 30:11.226
It's in pain,
and it's your responsibility.

30:11.227 --> 30:12.627
It was just an accident.

30:12.628 --> 30:15.128
If you walk away now,
it'll starve to death.

30:15.129 --> 30:17.287
Is that what you want?

30:21.736 --> 30:24.327
I'm not doing it.

30:29.744 --> 30:31.812
It's all right.

30:31.813 --> 30:35.143
- It's in heaven now.
- What's wrong with you?

30:42.390 --> 30:44.791
- Is the water warm enough?
- Yes, thank you.

30:44.792 --> 30:47.623
Okay. Call me if you need anything.

31:05.046 --> 31:07.209
Esther?

31:07.650 --> 31:09.983
Esther.

31:10.285 --> 31:12.352
Open this door.

31:15.658 --> 31:18.425
- What are you doing?
- I always lock the door.

31:18.426 --> 31:20.427
No, we don't lock doors
in this house.

31:20.428 --> 31:23.087
But what if someone comes in
and sees me?

31:23.298 --> 31:24.598
Nobody's gonna come in.

31:24.599 --> 31:27.801
Look, I'm gonna stand right here,
if that's what you want.

31:27.802 --> 31:29.504
I could sing for you.

31:29.505 --> 31:34.438
I used to sing for the sisters
so they would know I was all right.

31:36.345 --> 31:38.507
Okay.

31:38.613 --> 31:42.672
All right. But you know what?
This is just for tonight.

