01:02:52.520 --> 01:02:55.020
Do you wanna get that?

01:02:58.594 --> 01:03:00.927
<i>- Hello?
- Hello, is this Mrs. Coleman?</i>

01:03:00.928 --> 01:03:02.196
Yes. Who's this?

01:03:02.197 --> 01:03:04.298
This is Sister Judith
from St. Mariana's.

01:03:04.299 --> 01:03:06.668
I'm sorry to bother you,
but I need to know...

01:03:06.669 --> 01:03:09.705
if Sister Abigail
made it to her appointment with you.

01:03:09.706 --> 01:03:12.040
Yes. Why?

01:03:12.041 --> 01:03:14.076
<i>She hasn't returned since yesterday...</i>

01:03:14.077 --> 01:03:17.771
<i>and I'm just starting
to get really worried.</i>

01:03:27.726 --> 01:03:30.725
Charlie 24,
you wanna hold them there?

01:03:35.333 --> 01:03:37.324
Hey.

01:03:43.008 --> 01:03:45.543
Okay, I think we're done.

01:03:46.479 --> 01:03:50.115
Detective, do you have
any leads or suspects?

01:03:50.116 --> 01:03:54.120
- No, not yet.
- I just don't understand...

01:03:54.121 --> 01:03:56.821
this kind of thing.
Who would do this? It's...

01:03:56.822 --> 01:03:58.024
Awful.

01:03:58.025 --> 01:04:00.494
You think of anything else,
you give us a call.

01:04:00.495 --> 01:04:02.585
Yes. Absolutely.

01:04:02.862 --> 01:04:04.855
Let's go.

01:05:01.027 --> 01:05:04.363
This is what Sister Abigail
was talking about. Look.

01:05:04.364 --> 01:05:08.233
"Character-disturbed children".
Look at the symptoms.

01:05:08.234 --> 01:05:13.932
"Superficially charming. Difficulty
at making and keeping friends".

01:05:14.074 --> 01:05:16.010
I'm not sure this is what she meant.

01:05:16.011 --> 01:05:20.546
She could've told Dr. Browning
whatever she wanted to hear. Look.

01:05:22.550 --> 01:05:24.818
They "are adroit manipulators...

01:05:24.819 --> 01:05:28.822
oftentimes playing people off
one another to get what they want".

01:05:28.823 --> 01:05:31.225
Well, you gonna show this
to Dr. Browning?

01:05:31.226 --> 01:05:34.094
I'm not showing her anything.

01:05:34.095 --> 01:05:35.930
I'm not seeing her anymore.

01:05:35.931 --> 01:05:39.067
- When did you decide that?
- When do you think?

01:05:39.068 --> 01:05:41.102
You're gonna discount Dr. Browning?

01:05:41.103 --> 01:05:45.504
Why does everyone get the benefit
of the doubt from you except for me?

01:05:54.851 --> 01:05:58.088
If you need help with the kids,
we can arrange that.

01:05:58.089 --> 01:06:00.953
I don't need help.

01:06:09.368 --> 01:06:11.369
I just wanna know more about her.

01:06:11.370 --> 01:06:15.474
I wanna know where she came from,
and I wanna know who she is.

01:06:15.475 --> 01:06:17.876
What if Sister Abigail was right?

01:06:17.877 --> 01:06:20.813
I mean, if someone was in danger,
our own children...

01:06:20.814 --> 01:06:23.682
- wouldn't you wanna know?
- Of course I would.

01:06:23.683 --> 01:06:27.619
I'll contact the orphanage she came
from in Russia. All right?

01:06:27.620 --> 01:06:29.744
I mean, it's a start.

01:06:39.533 --> 01:06:42.761
- What?
- Hey.

01:06:48.611 --> 01:06:50.277
Fine.

01:06:50.278 --> 01:06:53.782
I was wondering if you'd heard from
anyone at the Sludyanka Shelter.

01:06:53.783 --> 01:06:57.018
Sister Abigail had mentioned
that she would...

01:06:57.019 --> 01:06:58.613
Oh, you did.

01:07:01.358 --> 01:07:05.155
I don't understand. How can they
have no record of her being there?

01:07:06.330 --> 01:07:07.797
Yes, please.

01:07:07.798 --> 01:07:12.528
Could you just call me as soon as
you know anything, please? Thank you.

01:07:43.904 --> 01:07:46.096
Esther, we gotta go.

01:07:52.179 --> 01:07:54.275
Esther?

01:07:57.884 --> 01:08:00.015
Esther?

01:08:01.055 --> 01:08:02.557
You got me.

01:08:05.294 --> 01:08:08.262
- What?
- I don't want to go to the dentist.

01:08:08.263 --> 01:08:11.065
- Why not?
- I just don't want to go.

01:08:11.066 --> 01:08:13.896
- What, are you scared?
- No.

01:08:15.206 --> 01:08:17.238
We're gonna reschedule, though.

01:08:17.238 --> 01:08:21.644
Tell you what, I'll let you play hooky
if you want to come and draw with me.

01:08:21.645 --> 01:08:23.979
All right.

01:08:27.251 --> 01:08:29.118
Wait, Daniel.

01:08:29.120 --> 01:08:33.176
How are you two getting along
with Esther?

01:08:35.093 --> 01:08:36.426
Fine, I guess.

01:08:36.428 --> 01:08:38.359
- Yeah?
- Yeah, Mom.

01:08:40.064 --> 01:08:44.269
But has she ever made you feel,
I don't know, uncomfortable...

01:08:44.270 --> 01:08:47.862
or has she done anything
that she's not supposed to do?

01:08:48.274 --> 01:08:53.004
- No.
- Like, has she ever hurt any of you?

01:08:53.546 --> 01:08:55.738
No.

01:08:58.685 --> 01:09:00.484
You sure?

01:09:03.558 --> 01:09:07.251
Okay. All right.

01:09:08.261 --> 01:09:11.064
I like it
when it's just the two of us.

01:09:11.064 --> 01:09:15.303
You don't know how long I've waited
for a daddy just like you.

01:09:15.304 --> 01:09:17.371
Mommy too, right?

01:09:18.773 --> 01:09:20.808
I don't think
Mommy likes me very much.

01:09:20.809 --> 01:09:22.377
Hey.

01:09:22.377 --> 01:09:25.113
- That is not true. Mommy loves you.
- It's all right.

01:09:25.113 --> 01:09:28.384
It must be hard to love an
adopted child as much as your own.

01:09:28.385 --> 01:09:33.444
Sweetheart, you're just as much a part
of this family as Danny and Max. Okay?

01:09:33.957 --> 01:09:37.359
Do something nice for Mommy.
Show her how much you love her.

01:09:37.361 --> 01:09:40.484
That's a wonderful idea.

01:09:59.519 --> 01:10:02.279
I have a special surprise
for you, Mommy.

01:10:02.654 --> 01:10:04.454
You do?

01:10:05.692 --> 01:10:09.022
I picked these flowers
just for you.

01:10:11.397 --> 01:10:17.536
- Esther, what did you do? God.
- My arm!

01:10:17.537 --> 01:10:19.072
- Why did you do this?
- Daddy, my arm!

01:10:20.642 --> 01:10:21.941
- John!
- Hey.

01:10:21.942 --> 01:10:25.145
- What did you do?
- Hey. Stop, stop.

01:10:25.146 --> 01:10:26.380
Why did you do this?

01:10:26.381 --> 01:10:29.650
- Oh, God. God, she did this on purpose.
- No, no, no.

01:10:29.651 --> 01:10:31.251
- Yes, she did.
- Hey. Honey, no.

01:10:31.252 --> 01:10:33.854
She knew
what these roses meant to me.

01:10:33.855 --> 01:10:37.358
It's my fault, hon. I told her
to do something nice for you.

01:10:37.359 --> 01:10:39.655
I can't believe this.

01:12:21.271 --> 01:12:24.136
Daddy!

01:12:24.275 --> 01:12:26.939
Daddy!

01:12:27.680 --> 01:12:30.349
Daddy, Daddy!

01:12:30.350 --> 01:12:32.006
What is it, honey?

01:12:32.050 --> 01:12:34.811
My arm still hurts.

01:12:39.158 --> 01:12:42.795
Can I have a look at it?
You're okay.

01:12:42.796 --> 01:12:45.396
I'll be gentle.
It's all right, honey.

01:12:45.397 --> 01:12:47.561
Oh, my God.

01:12:49.035 --> 01:12:52.127
We need to take you
to the hospital.

01:12:56.110 --> 01:12:58.713
You're a brave little girl,
you know that?

01:12:58.714 --> 01:13:02.111
Doctor said
you're gonna heal real fast, okay?

01:13:18.034 --> 01:13:19.829
You broke her arm.

01:13:23.339 --> 01:13:25.642
It's impossible.
I didn't grab her that hard.

01:13:25.643 --> 01:13:31.340
She wants to sleep in here tonight.
Maybe you should sleep downstairs.

01:13:50.669 --> 01:13:53.704
I'm having guests for dinner.

01:13:57.244 --> 01:14:00.540
You know,
you can have it. Thanks.

01:15:03.348 --> 01:15:06.178
Have a good day.

01:15:13.494 --> 01:15:15.260
Daniel.

01:15:15.261 --> 01:15:17.389
Your books.

01:15:20.500 --> 01:15:24.366
- What happened? Let me see your bag.
- I don't know.

01:15:26.040 --> 01:15:30.134
We just bought this.
Pick it up, it's gonna get wet.

01:15:36.118 --> 01:15:38.178
Mom!

01:15:39.988 --> 01:15:43.820
Max! No! Help!

01:15:44.726 --> 01:15:46.695
Max!

01:15:48.297 --> 01:15:50.255
Max!

01:16:02.213 --> 01:16:04.171
Max!

01:16:11.289 --> 01:16:13.323
Max!

01:16:13.324 --> 01:16:15.259
Are you okay?

01:16:15.260 --> 01:16:18.796
I'm here. Mommy's here.
You're okay, honey. Come on.

01:16:18.797 --> 01:16:24.358
I got you. Yeah. Oh, baby,
it's okay. I'm so sorry.

01:16:25.804 --> 01:16:28.474
I remember I put it in park
and I set the brake.

01:16:28.475 --> 01:16:31.344
Max didn't indicate
that Esther did anything.

01:16:31.345 --> 01:16:36.615
Well, Max is covering for her.
And I don't think it's the first time.

01:16:36.616 --> 01:16:40.744
It also wouldn't be the first time
you blamed Esther for your own mistake.

01:16:43.691 --> 01:16:46.326
You know what?
I want her out of this house.

01:16:46.327 --> 01:16:48.762
You're ready for somebody
to come and take her?

01:16:48.763 --> 01:16:51.366
I am. I don't care.

01:16:51.367 --> 01:16:55.368
I will do whatever it takes
to protect my children.

01:16:55.369 --> 01:16:57.666
The girls found this this morning.

01:16:58.007 --> 01:17:00.875
The girls found it.
You mean Esther found it.

01:17:00.876 --> 01:17:03.678
Yes, Esther. Does it make
any difference? Is she lying?

01:17:03.679 --> 01:17:04.980
You need help.

01:17:04.981 --> 01:17:08.183
We've reserved a place for you
in a rehabilitation facility...

01:17:08.184 --> 01:17:10.686
about 45 minutes from here.

01:17:10.687 --> 01:17:12.220
I didn't drink it.

01:17:12.221 --> 01:17:15.824
I bought two bottles.
I poured one of them down the sink.

01:17:15.825 --> 01:17:17.727
- But not this one?
- No.

01:17:17.728 --> 01:17:21.697
John, I haven't had a drink
in almost a year.

01:17:21.698 --> 01:17:24.334
We wanna help you,
but there's nothing we can do...

01:17:24.335 --> 01:17:28.604
- until you stop lying to yourself.
- I'm not lying. I wanted to drink it.

01:17:28.605 --> 01:17:32.342
You have no fucking idea how badly
I wanted to drink it, but I didn't.

01:17:32.343 --> 01:17:34.878
- I didn't drink it.
- If Max had gotten hurt...

01:17:34.879 --> 01:17:38.650
What happened this morning
has nothing to do with this.

01:17:38.651 --> 01:17:40.843
I find that hard to believe.

01:17:41.020 --> 01:17:45.785
The only reason that I'm sober
is because of Max and Daniel.

01:17:46.259 --> 01:17:49.995
I think about what would have
happened had you not been there...

01:17:49.996 --> 01:17:52.198
and it makes me wanna kill myself.

01:17:52.199 --> 01:17:54.133
I would never do anything...

01:17:54.134 --> 01:17:57.369
to let something like that
ever happen again. I wouldn't.

01:17:57.370 --> 01:17:59.840
That is so manipulative.

01:17:59.841 --> 01:18:03.375
I know I haven't given you reason
to believe me, I know I haven't.

01:18:03.376 --> 01:18:05.879
I lied to you.
I should have told you about this.

01:18:05.880 --> 01:18:09.383
I'll go to therapy, I'll go to fucking
A.A. if that's what you want...

01:18:09.384 --> 01:18:11.918
- but you have to believe me.
- I don't.

01:18:11.919 --> 01:18:14.923
You have to believe me.
John, you have to trust me on this.

01:18:14.924 --> 01:18:17.525
I'll give you a week
to go to rehab...

01:18:17.526 --> 01:18:20.228
or I'm leaving
and I'm taking the kids with me.

01:18:20.229 --> 01:18:22.597
I think that's fair, okay?

01:18:22.598 --> 01:18:25.300
I'll help you as much as I can,
make it really easy.

01:18:25.301 --> 01:18:27.269
Mom's gonna come in the afternoon.

01:18:27.270 --> 01:18:32.408
All right? I'm willing to do this.
I'm willing to try and figure this out.

01:18:32.409 --> 01:18:36.808
- But it's up to you.
- I'll shoot Mommy if you tell.

01:18:57.136 --> 01:19:00.432
Max. Max, are you okay?

01:19:01.008 --> 01:19:05.099
What did she do? Did she do something
to make the car crash?

01:19:06.212 --> 01:19:11.083
If you saw her, you have to help me,
so Mom and Dad can protect us.

01:19:13.620 --> 01:19:15.214
Why not?

01:19:23.999 --> 01:19:26.691
Is that Sister Abigail?

01:19:33.242 --> 01:19:36.744
Max. What did she do
in my tree house?

01:19:38.982 --> 01:19:41.276
Are the bad things still there?

01:19:44.020 --> 01:19:46.155
Everything's gonna be okay.

01:19:46.156 --> 01:19:51.490
I'll get the stuff from the tree house.
Then they'll have to believe us.

01:20:38.046 --> 01:20:41.448
- Going somewhere, Kate?
- What are you doing here?

01:20:41.449 --> 01:20:44.119
She's fine. Let's not wake her.

01:20:44.120 --> 01:20:45.453
Go to your room.

01:20:45.454 --> 01:20:49.190
Honestly, we're past that now.
Aren't we?

01:20:49.191 --> 01:20:51.850
I know what you're doing.

01:20:52.429 --> 01:20:54.461
I will not let you
hurt my children.

01:20:54.462 --> 01:20:55.865
Me?

01:20:55.866 --> 01:20:59.634
I'm not the one who passed out drunk
and let Max almost drown in the pond.

01:20:59.635 --> 01:21:01.237
If it wasn't for John...

01:21:01.238 --> 01:21:05.638
she'd be dead,
and you'd probably still be in jail.

01:21:06.978 --> 01:21:08.669
Who told you that?

01:21:10.781 --> 01:21:12.576
It's very intimate.

01:21:12.917 --> 01:21:14.751
- I learned so much.
- Give it to me.

01:21:14.752 --> 01:21:18.456
- Jessica. Your cheating husband.
- Esther, give it to me.

01:21:18.457 --> 01:21:20.425
Where you hide your wine bottles.

01:21:20.426 --> 01:21:22.927
I'm... I'm warning you
right now.

01:21:22.928 --> 01:21:25.430
"She was still kicking
when the doctor told me...

01:21:25.431 --> 01:21:28.300
it was something called phantom...

01:21:28.301 --> 01:21:29.934
fetal movement.

01:21:29.935 --> 01:21:33.773
- For 16 days, I carried my dead baby".
- Stop it. Esther.

01:21:33.774 --> 01:21:37.176
" It was the cruelest torture
I could imagine".

01:21:37.177 --> 01:21:39.779
Stop it. You stop it.

01:21:39.780 --> 01:21:42.080
What's wrong with you?

01:21:42.081 --> 01:21:45.018
Kate, it's too late.
It's your own fault.

01:21:45.019 --> 01:21:47.280
You took your family for granted.

01:21:47.288 --> 01:21:51.017
- What do you mean?
- What are you going to do?

01:21:52.093 --> 01:21:54.189
Hit me?

01:21:59.534 --> 01:22:02.770
We adopted her from you.
How could you not know anything?

01:22:02.771 --> 01:22:05.206
The Sullivans
could have adopted her illegally.

01:22:05.207 --> 01:22:08.777
<i>She doesn't remember anything
that could help us?</i>

01:22:10.045 --> 01:22:12.136
I'm gonna call you back.

01:23:28.999 --> 01:23:32.465
"Saarne Institute".

01:23:50.956 --> 01:23:54.926
Hello. Do you speak English?

01:23:56.628 --> 01:23:58.463
Do you speak English?

01:23:58.464 --> 01:24:00.632
Is there anyone
who speaks English there?

01:24:00.633 --> 01:24:02.767
This is very important.

01:24:06.672 --> 01:24:08.637
I don't know what you're saying.

01:24:21.354 --> 01:24:23.856
- Hello?
- Is this the Saarne Institute?

01:24:23.857 --> 01:24:25.591
<i>Yes.</i>

01:24:25.592 --> 01:24:29.195
Yes. I need to talk to somebody
about one of your children.

01:24:29.196 --> 01:24:31.998
She was adopted by an American family.
It's a girl.

01:24:31.999 --> 01:24:35.301
<i>She is not come from here.</i>

01:24:35.302 --> 01:24:37.604
Well, I haven't even
told you her name yet.

01:24:37.605 --> 01:24:40.641
You do not understand.
Saarne Institute is not an orphanage.

01:24:40.642 --> 01:24:42.607
It is a mental hospital.

01:25:10.041 --> 01:25:12.610
Are you looking for this?

01:25:14.211 --> 01:25:16.211
Poor Sister Abigail.

01:25:16.814 --> 01:25:21.753
I couldn't have done it myself,
you know. Max is just as guilty as I am.

01:25:21.754 --> 01:25:25.623
- Whatever Max did, you made her do it.
- Think about it.

01:25:25.624 --> 01:25:28.716
How did she even know
what was up here?

01:25:28.727 --> 01:25:32.065
It's always better
to burn the evidence.

01:25:32.066 --> 01:25:37.134
If they find these things,
they won't just be coming for me.

01:25:37.135 --> 01:25:39.466
They'll be coming for Max too.

01:25:40.341 --> 01:25:42.839
- Is that really what you want?
- Wait.

01:25:44.044 --> 01:25:45.975
What're you doing?

01:25:46.580 --> 01:25:48.773
Are you crazy?

01:25:54.857 --> 01:25:56.356
Let me out!

01:25:56.357 --> 01:25:58.789
Let me out of here!

01:26:08.538 --> 01:26:11.930
Mom!

01:26:12.042 --> 01:26:17.246
It's called the Saarne Institute.
S~A~A~R~N~E, Saarne.

01:26:17.247 --> 01:26:18.680
<i>It's in Estonia.</i>

01:26:18.681 --> 01:26:23.420
Estonia? No, this can't be right.
All of her paperwork is from Russia.

01:26:23.421 --> 01:26:25.988
I'm sending them a picture
of her right now.

01:26:25.989 --> 01:26:28.925
Maybe her birth mother
was a patient there.

01:26:28.926 --> 01:26:32.086
I don't know.
Maybe she was even born there.

01:26:36.835 --> 01:26:39.294
Mom!

01:26:39.705 --> 01:26:42.973
Help!

01:26:58.724 --> 01:27:01.355
Mom! Dad!

01:27:08.335 --> 01:27:10.038
Oh, God!

01:27:19.114 --> 01:27:21.876
Oh, God. Call 911!

01:27:33.163 --> 01:27:36.288
Don't worry.
You're going to heaven.

01:27:38.403 --> 01:27:40.764
Oh, God!

01:27:42.507 --> 01:27:47.566
Oh, my God! Daniel!

01:27:47.578 --> 01:27:50.180
Move away! Move away from the fire!

01:27:50.181 --> 01:27:51.415
Daniel?

01:27:51.416 --> 01:27:55.887
Oh, God, no. Daniel?
Mommy's right here. Can you hear me?

01:27:55.888 --> 01:27:59.058
Please wake up.
Honey, Mommy's right here, okay?

01:27:59.059 --> 01:28:01.888
You're gonna be all right.

01:28:11.672 --> 01:28:16.108
We stopped the abdominal bleeding,
but he has a very serious neck injury.

01:28:16.109 --> 01:28:20.348
He's stabilized for now. You should
consider yourselves very lucky.

01:28:20.349 --> 01:28:22.883
- Can we see him?
- In a little while.

01:28:22.884 --> 01:28:25.018
He's resting in the ICU.

01:28:25.019 --> 01:28:28.623
Okay. And will he be able
to tell us what happened?

01:28:28.624 --> 01:28:30.357
It's possible.

01:28:30.358 --> 01:28:34.053
No way of knowing for sure what
he'll remember until he wakes up.

01:28:34.230 --> 01:28:36.220
Excuse me.

01:28:38.601 --> 01:28:41.032
It's gonna be okay.

01:28:44.207 --> 01:28:48.478
JOHN: I know you're exhausted
and upset, and so am I.

01:28:48.479 --> 01:28:52.447
There has to be some other explanation.
She didn't come from an insane asylum.

01:28:52.448 --> 01:28:56.953
The orphanage you thought
she came from has never heard of her.

01:28:56.954 --> 01:28:58.888
Everything about her could be a lie.

01:28:58.889 --> 01:29:02.057
We have her passport. We have
school records, medical records.

01:29:02.058 --> 01:29:04.361
These are papers
from around the world.

01:29:04.362 --> 01:29:06.564
What is this?
It's a piece of paper.

01:29:06.565 --> 01:29:11.397
Your own mother was there this time. It
wasn't just me. Your mother was there.

01:29:11.436 --> 01:29:14.506
It's either Esther
or Daniel who started the fire.

01:29:14.507 --> 01:29:17.442
